@startuml
title Domain Planner v1 Provider Flow

actor "HomeTusk Backend" as HomeTusk
participant "AI Platform /v1/decide" as Decide
participant "CommandDTO Validator" as CommandValidator
participant "Domain Planner v1\n(narrow corridor)" as Planner
participant "DecisionDTO Validator" as DecisionValidator
participant "Provider Eval\n(seed scenarios)" as Eval

HomeTusk -> Decide: CommandDTO\nreviewed text + minimal context
Decide -> CommandValidator: validate request schema
CommandValidator --> Decide: valid / reject request

Decide -> Planner: plan within narrow corridor
Planner -> Planner: create_task / add_shopping_items / clarify / first-class safe reject
Planner --> Decide: provider DecisionDTO candidate

Decide -> DecisionValidator: validate response schema
DecisionValidator --> Decide: schema-valid DecisionDTO
Decide --> HomeTusk: provider decision + trace/version metadata

HomeTusk -> HomeTusk: map to accepted taxonomy
HomeTusk -> HomeTusk: schema validation, guardrails,\nexecution authority, DecisionLog

Eval ..> Decide: offline seed scenario run
Eval ..> Eval: scenario IDs, metrics,\nfailure buckets, no raw text reports

note over Planner
AI Platform does not mutate HomeTusk state.
No direct mobile/web calls to AI Platform.
ASR remains transcription-only and does not auto-call /v1/decide.
end note

@enduml
